===Etymology===
Derived from Greek '''tele''', meaning "far off", and '''cine''', meaning "motion" (the same root as '''[[cinema]]''')

===Noun===
{{Wikipedia}}
'''telecine'''

#''Filmology.'' The process of transferring [[motion picture]] [[film]] into electronic form.
#A machine used to carry out this process.

===Verb===
'''to telecine''' (''past participle'' '''telecineed''', ''present participle'' '''telecineing'')

#To transfer (motion picture film) into electronic form.

